The Ona of Abaji and Chairman of the FCT Council of Traditional Rulers, His Royal Majesty (HRM), Alhaji Adamu Baba Yunusa, has appealed to the Director General of the National Information Technology Development Agency (NITDA) Dr. Isa Ali Ibrahim Pantami, to consider the indigenes of the territory for the agency’s scholarship scheme. Alhaji Yunusa, made the request when he paid a courtesy call on the Pantami at the agency’s headquarters last Thursday in Abuja. He also commended the leadership of the Director-General of the National Information Technology Development Agency (NITDA). OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE He said informed the NITDA DG that was at the agency’s headquarters to explore possible areas of collaboration, which he said was aimed at deepening the growth of ICT in the various  FCT Councils. In his response, the Director General of NITDA, Dr Isa Ali Ibrahim Pantami, thanked the traditional for the commendation, stressing that it is a motivation for him to do more. Dr Pantami said that “there is no discrimination in NITDA, FCT is considered as a state”, adding that the Agency’s Scholarship Scheme and intervention projects are in line with the principles of federal character.  NITDA saved N2.5bn through IT project clearance – DG MDAs use IT projects to siphon funds, NITDA tells EFCC NITDA saved N2.5bn through IT project clearance in 2017 - DG Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin